Pronotal collar and anterior pronotal lobe dark brown, posterior pronotal lobe brown with the posterior lateral angles lighter; pronotum punctate, with most prominent punctures on posterior pronotal lobe; with very short setae; anterior pronotal lobe very elongate (
Figs. 1, 3
), collar delimited posteriorly by a row of punctures in a groove. Length collar, anterior and posterior pronotal lobe 0.18, 1.00, 0.73 respectively. Width collar, anterior and posterior pronotal lobe 0.77, 1.08, 1.62 respectively. Scutellum dark brown; with a Yshape carina, protuberant medially. Length scutellum 1.08, width 0.90.
